Cyclophora maderensis is a moth in the  family Geometridae. It is found on the Canary Islands and Madeira.The wingspan is 18â€“25 mm. The forewings are ochreous, finely and densely irrorated with rough pinkish scales. There is a central waved band with a grey hue and a paler ochre subterminal line. The hindwings are also ochreous.
The larvae feed on Erica species, including Erica arborea.